- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper also investigates the complexity of algorithmic problems related to the game, which could fall under this category.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The game is based on a regular target language, and the paper studies conditions for winning strategies in a context-free game, making this category a possibility.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper involves studying the existence of dominant or undominated strategies, which could fall under this category.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper investigates the complexity of algorithmic problems related to the game, which could also fall under this category.
